<font color="#FF0000">JUST LIKE MOM USED TO FIX!</font><br>
<tt>Sun Sep 14 12:13:55 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I remember going to some rather remote places, on days when I flew ash and trash.  I always took several bags of hard candy and some extra C's along.<br>
I would pass this shit out to starving children.. I didn't give a shit if they were V.C. kids or not.. they were children... they were starving and they were pitiful.<br>
My crewchief said, &quot;Sir, you're pretty slick!&quot; <br>
I asked him, &quot;Why do you say that?&quot;<br>
He replied, &quot;What sniper would take a shot at you..when you are surrounded by all those kids.<br>
He meant no harm in saying that..it was good logic and made sense.<br>
I wanted to scream in his face, &quot;I don't give a shit about being shot.. I just want these kids to eat!&quot;  I didn't have the guts to tell him that I was trying to wash away some guilt for having already killed too many children.  But, I didn't say anything.  I just nodded my head and felt more shame.  I kept thinking &quot;Damned if you do and damned if you don't!&quot;<br>
Without speaking, he helped me pass out the meager offerings.  I think he felt good about it.  He always wanted me to fly his ship.. until he died flying with another crew.<br>
That's just the way it was.. and will always be.<br><br>
M24
<p><code>-- love thy enemy...  (Stupid idiot!) </code><p>


